---

8. Multi-Service Architecture for Render Free

Redesign the system architecture to maximize compatibility with Render Free.

The system must be split into independent services.

Main Service

The Main Service should contain only lightweight components.

Responsibilities:

- Website
- Login
- Registration
- User management
- API key management
- Usage statistics
- Billing support (future)
- Admin dashboard
- Request routing
- Rate limiting

This service should consume as little RAM and CPU as possible.

It should never directly execute the language model.

---

AI Service

Create one or more independent AI services.

Responsibilities:

- SmolLM2 inference
- Memory retrieval
- Vector memory retrieval
- Knowledge database retrieval
- Prompt construction
- Final response generation

The AI service should expose an internal API used only by the Main Service.

---

Future Expansion

The architecture must allow multiple AI servers.

Example:

AI Server 1

AI Server 2

AI Server 3

...

The Main Service should be able to distribute requests between AI servers.

The routing system must be modular so additional AI servers can be added without modifying existing code.

---

9. AI Load Balancing

Implement a lightweight load balancing system.

Requirements:

- Detect which AI server is available.
- Distribute users between available AI servers.
- Prefer servers with the lowest current workload.
- Skip unavailable servers automatically.
- Retry another AI server if one fails.
- Keep the architecture scalable.

The goal is to improve concurrent request handling rather than increasing the size of a single AI model.

---

10. Render Sleep Awareness

Design the architecture specifically for Render Free.

Requirements:

- Assume AI services may enter sleep mode.
- Handle cold starts gracefully.
- Show an appropriate loading state while an AI server wakes up.
- Automatically retry requests after an AI service becomes available.
- Keep the Main Service responsive even while waiting.

---

11. Smart Request Routing

Before sending a request to an AI server, determine whether AI is actually required.

Examples:

Calculator

↓

Built-in calculation

Current date

↓

System function

Weather

↓

Weather API

Search

↓

Search API

Memory question

↓

Memory retrieval

Knowledge question

↓

Knowledge database

Creative writing

↓

AI Service

Only use the language model when necessary.

---

12. AI Service Scalability

The architecture must support horizontal scaling.

It should be possible to deploy multiple AI services independently.

The Main Service should automatically recognize available AI services from a configuration file or service registry.

Adding or removing AI servers should require no source code modifications.

---

13. Fault Tolerance

If one AI service crashes or becomes unavailable:

- Automatically redirect requests to another available AI service.
- Log the failure.
- Continue serving users whenever possible.

The failure of one AI service must not stop the entire platform.

---

Final Architecture Goal

The platform should behave like a professional distributed AI system.

Use lightweight independent services instead of one large server.

Optimize for:

- Render Free compatibility
- Low RAM usage
- Low CPU usage
- Scalability
- Reliability
- Fast response time
- Easy future expansion
